profile_positions.description:
Accelerating the transformation of Wolters Kluwer’s Finance, Risk and Regulatory Reporting (FRR) business from technology-driven to user-centred:

* Developing, managing & enabling execution of  a strong UX strategy;
* Identifying talent needs, growing business UX team from 1 IC shop to a strong , high-performing, homogenous, confident team of +/- 5 designers & researchers T.D.;
* Leading customer-centric design of expert solutions & strategic initiatives across the full E2E;
* Evangelising & building robust business cases for UX, across multiple business verticals; 
* Managing pipeline & portfolio of FRR design initiatives towards both growth & retention;
* Driving the application of lean principles to streamline workflows, prioritise customer needs, and maximise value delivered by products across multiple value streams; 
* Reducing UX debt, eliminating design waste &  improving efficiency by driving adoption of the Global Wolters Kluwer product design system;
*Design community-building around CX/UX, best practices, standards, shared experiences & opportunities;

Digital Society School is an innovation hub supporting organisations in developing the means necessary to guide digital transformation  - through delivering and advising on digital products, services, experiences, through knowledge sharing and trainings. Our partners are large public/quasi-public institutions and companies in the EU - operating in industries ranging from retail banking, to professional sports, public health, LegalTech, RegTech, policy...

* Grew, mentored and led a cross-functional team of 5-10 designers and engineers of whom I am immensely proud and respectful of. They are also great fun and expert pun creators <3;
* Identified and took advantage of new market opportunities that led to a new product and service offering, with significant revenue increase and consistent growth to customer/partner base;
* Transformed an internal support unit into a revenue generating, value-adding team, 2nd largest revenue generator in organisation within 2 years;
* Reduced service and maintenance effort & costs by implementing an operational paradigm focused on digital self-service, tooling, robust documentation and standardised support to internal teams - freeing up time and headspace to focus on value-add activities across DSS units; 
* Set, operationalised and championed the DSS strategy towards design and technology together with C-suite in a dedicated change-management cluster;
* Developed a new partnership model in close collaboration with Business Development and C-suite;
* Developed and operationalised an internal design process & services stack for instruments team in order to generate growth; 
* Led discovery, intake, brief generation sessions with prospects incl. negotiated and closed multiple multi-year deals with large public and quasi-public European, or national institutions;
* Led successful design & delivery of key instruments projects across 4+ partner segments.

* Design, research, development of the Digital Society School online courses platform, incl LMS vendor evaluation and selection;
* Development of the Adaptable Mindset course learning environment & assignments;
* Developed communication strategy for courses and spearheaded hiring relevant people to be able to further develop MarCom capabilities- creative/production designer, content marketeer
* Advocated for and ran POCs for setting up a new operational paradigm for providing internal templates that empower Digital Society School teams to do their work in an effective manner.
* Led research, design & development of the Digital Society Monitor initiative
